                  </persName>
            , an officer, produced the property, which was deposed to by the prosecutor.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. The prosecutor asked us to go up stairs and have a game at cards, and that he had some very nice ale, and we went up stairs, and played at cards, there were some other people playing at cards, and as we were coming down stairs, the woman of the house I believe saw some things lying upon the stairs, and she said I had taken them.</p>
               <p>The prisoner called his serjeant, who gave him a good character. <rs id="t18000402-75-verdict416" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18000402-75-verdict416" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. (Aged 26.)</p>
